      },
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh convergence study performed (coarse: 42k elements, medium: 168k elements, fine: 672k elements) using hex-dominant meshing with element size ratio 2. GCI for construct stiffness on fine mesh = 0.87%; yield force GCI = 1.14%. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Production runs use the fine mesh. Gradation 3 achieved."
