    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-nse",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error as a distinct credibility factor addresses iterative convergence tolerances and time-integration errors that arise in nonlinear dynamic or transient analyses. The present FEA model uses a quasi-static implicit formulation with a single load step and a direct sparse solver (Ansys SPARSE). Direct solvers do not accumulate iterative residual error; there is no time-stepping scheme and therefore no time-integration truncation error. The only relevant numerical error — discretization — is addressed separately under the Discretization error factor. Accordingly, Numerical solver error is not applicable to this deterministic implicit-static structural analysis and no required or achieved level is assigned."
    },
    {
