        "description": "The constitutive model (material law) for titanium alloy must be justified by published mechanical property data and a documented sensitivity study showing that QoI variation due to constitutive model choice is <5% across the plausible range of Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus (110–120 GPa)."
      },
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive model applied to Ti-6Al-4V (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.14 GPa) consistent with ASTM F136 property ranges. Sensitivity study varying elastic modulus from 110 to 120 GPa shows <3.2% variation in stiffness QoI and <2.8% in yield force QoI. Polyethylene test block modeled as linear elastic (E=1.0 GPa) per ASTM F1717 specification. Model form selection justified by published Ti-6Al-4V data (Donachie 2000) and prior FDA FEA studies. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
