        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — measured geometry and material traceability",
        "description": "Geometric inputs must be derived from CMM measurements of the actual test specimens (±0.01 mm tolerance). Material property inputs must be traceable to certificate of conformance (CoC) or published ASTM F136 ranges. Input uncertainty must be propagated to QoI uncertainty."
      },
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry inputs derived from CMM measurements of three representative specimens from the N=11 test lot (mean ± 1σ reported). Material property inputs (E, σ_y, E_t) sourced from DePuy Synthes material CoC for the specific manufacturing lot. Input uncertainty propagated via ±1σ Monte Carlo sampling (500 runs); 95th-percentile QoI uncertainty bands reported in Appendix C. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
