        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria — production-representative specimens across two labs",
        "description": "Test specimens must be production-representative (same manufacturing lot, same surface finish, same sterilization state as the device intended for market). N≥10 specimens must be tested. Testing must be performed at a minimum of two independent laboratories to detect inter-lab variability."
      },
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested; specimens drawn from the same manufacturing lot as the 510(k) submission device. Surface finish and ETO sterilization state identical to commercial device. Testing distributed across two independent laboratories (FDA OSEL biomechanics lab and an ISO 17025-accredited contract laboratory). Inter-lab coefficient of variation for stiffness <4.1%, confirming specimen and protocol consistency. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
