        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — multiple load cases spanning COU envelope",
        "description": "Testing must span at least two distinct load levels or construct configurations representative of the clinical use envelope (e.g., varying rod diameter or screw spacing). A single ASTM F1717 standard test condition is insufficient to demonstrate model predictive capability across the COU."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending condition (axial compressive load applied at 5°, 100 mm moment arm). No alternative rod diameters or screw spacings were tested experimentally, limiting the breadth of model validation to a single operating point. This shortfall relative to Gradation 3 is acknowledged; offset rationale is provided in the decision record. Gradation 2 achieved."
