        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria — simulation inputs match experimental conditions",
        "description": "All simulation boundary conditions and material inputs must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test setup. Discrepancies between nominal FEA inputs and measured experimental values must be quantified and shown to contribute <5% to QoI uncertainty."
      },
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions (load application point, fixture geometry, polyethylene block modulus) verified against laboratory fixture drawings and calibration records. Measured screw insertion torque and rod pre-stress are within 2% of FEA assumed values. Sensitivity analysis confirms that residual input discrepancies contribute <3.8% to stiffness QoI uncertainty. Equivalency confirmed for all three QoIs. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-oc",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-cou1-oc-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — quantitative metric with uncertainty",
        "description": "QoI agreement must be assessed using a quantitative validation metric that accounts for both experimental and simulation uncertainty. The validation metric E/u_val must be <1.96 for each QoI (95% confidence interval criterion). Percent difference must be <10% for each QoI."
      },
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison performed for all three QoIs using the ASME V&V 20 validation metric E/u_val. Results: stiffness E/u_val=0.83 (3.1% difference), yield force E/u_val=1.12 (5.4% difference), force at 40 mm E/u_val=0.97 (4.8% difference). All metrics satisfy E/u_val<1.96 and <10% difference criteria. Uncertainty in experimental mean computed from N=11 specimens (95% CI); simulation uncertainty from Monte Carlo propagation. Gradation 4 achieved: structured uncertainty-inclusive metric applied across all QoIs with full documentation."
    },
    {
