      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-cou1-rqi-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria — QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes",
        "description": "The selected QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) must be demonstrably linked to the clinical failure modes of concern (fatigue fracture, screw loosening). The linkage must be documented in the simulation plan with reference to published clinical evidence."
      },
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three ASTM F1717-specified QoIs for static compression-bending and are directly linked to the clinical failure modes of pedicle screw fatigue fracture and construct loosening, as documented in the simulation plan (Section 2.3) with reference to Fogel et al. (2014) and Galbusera et al. (2015). All three QoIs are measurable in the F1717 bench test and are computed by the FEA model. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-rva",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The 'Relevance of the validation activities to the COU' factor is intended to assess whether the validation scenario — including patient population, anatomical site, and loading environment — differs from the intended clinical COU in ways that could limit transferability of the validation evidence. In this package, the validation activity IS the COU: the FEA model is validated directly against the ASTM F1717 bench test protocol, which is itself the regulatory submission test method for this device class. There is no gap between the validation domain and the COU domain because the bench test and the model prediction share identical geometry, loading, and boundary conditions by construction. Accordingly, a separate relevance assessment would be vacuous and this factor is not applicable. No required or achieved level is assigned."
